RIYADH: Dubai Investments Co. earned 50 million dirhams ($258 million) from the Emicool deal it concluded earlier, the company’s CEO told Al-Arabiya. Khalid bin Kalban said the company will use the funds in debt reduction, paying exceptional profits to shareholders and making further investments. The company sold a 50 percent stake in Emirates District Cooling Co., known as Emicool, to Actis Investment Co. in a deal valued at 1.2 billion dirhams. Emicool has a corporate valuation of 3.7 billion dirhams and equity valuation of 2.4 billion. Established in 2003 as a wholly-owned subsidiary of Dubai Investments, Emicool provides district cooling services in the UAE with 30 percent market share.